			  			<HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  			1) In the next set, will images be added such that there won't be an animated banner saying &quot;No Image&quot; on almost every page?<br />
<br />
2) Can someone explain to me the point of designing ships? Being able to add 11 slots worth of Homing Black Holes, Eternium, and devices on a Doomstar with set engines and shiedling doesn't sound like much strategy to me. The techs you add to a ship don't affect how much it costs or how long it takes to build the ship; it seems that there's no resource management at all in designing ships, just sticking the best of whatever you have at the time onto the biggest ship you can afford to build. I say this not because I'm complaining at the game but because I once played a game similar to Archspace where designing ships involved both skill and resource management because the technologies you added would affect so many things and even had complicated synergy effects with each other. I remember working on ships for that game so often online and offonline that one of my teachers thought it was quantum physics work because of the Archspace-like vocabulary(e.g. &quot;tachyon projection&quot;, &quot;quantum synthesis&quot;, &quot;spatial strand&quot;). This doesn't happen for me in Archspace because it takes me no more than five minutes to design a Doomstar like everyone else's once I finish teching. Then again, maybe I'm just stupid and missing something here.<br />
<br />
Thanks in advance for any answers.						<P align=right> </P>
					</TD>
				</TR>
	
		
