			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	2) Yes, ship design may seem a little simplistic for advanced players. But there is a lot of variety actually, you just need to find out ;)<br />
<br />
Ok, design is mostly &quot;missile-based&quot;, i.e Fusion -&gt; Amm -&gt; Nova -&gt; HBH. <br />
<br />
DB, NRL, OOD kicks in a lot later and is only really   worthful in 20 vs 20 doom battles which are rare. But still ;)<br />
<br />
However, its really NOT about always build the biggest, that's probably the biggest mistake you can do. Esp in the beginning the smallest ships are the most powerful resource wise (400 missile GB beat 40 missile Frigs easily and so on). Of course, you need to find a good compromise between power level (fluff), the numbers you can fit on a fleet (max. 20 fleets) and a commander (max. 40).<br />
There is a lot of skill involved here.			   <P align=right></P>
			</TD>
