			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Well, projectile and beam weapons have their value thoughout the game if used well. You never know when your projectile/beam backup fleets will save your ass in combat, generally being after all HBH has fired off and both side(s) are waiting to fire again. Especially true if both sides take considerable damage, as neither really has a significant advantage over the other. Keep in mind that Projectile/Beam do more considerably more damage than missiles over time, and if used well against opponents, can be used to compensate for the lack of fire power and/or technology. I did fine using pure DB dreads 2 sets ago for a couple of days while I waited to get HBH. When I finally did get broken though, I took a decent number of dooms down with me. ;p<br />
<br />
When you produce ships slowly, some people build mixed designs so that they can more effectively gain the bonuses of having both DB and HBH, and not be screwed if they lose all of a certain type, etc. Also not bad if your aim with that design is a more defensive one, and you aim for strong shields or higher/stronger hp/armor. Up to individual players really. Different things work for different people. Generally though, yeah, pure missile is a fav thing to do, and works quite well. Try it late game though, and you're asking for an ass-kicking. ;p Unless you have a massssive advantage, and quite literally shoot all or almost all your HBH BEFORE the enemy gets a shot off. Though, as we saw, remaining Xeru NRL dooms can easilly cut through the enemy's dooms. ;p Which makes NRL a very powerful comeback weapon that can easilly win the battle for you. PSL will be stronger next set as well.			   <P align=right></P>
